Update Set
Overview

An Update Set is a ServiceNow feature used to capture and migrate configuration changes from one ServiceNow instance to another. It allows developers to package customizations such as tables, roles, ACLs, workflows, and application configurations.

This project uses an Update Set to store all the configurations required for the implementation of the Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) system.

Components Included

The Update Set contains the following configurations:

- User Configuration
- Group Configuration
- Custom Roles
- Role Assignments
- Project Task Table
- Custom Fields
- Access Control Lists (ACLs)
- Flow Designer Workflow
- Notification Configuration
- Application Customizations

 Purpose

The Update Set helps in:

- Migrating project configurations between ServiceNow instances.
- Maintaining version control of customizations.
- Simplifying deployment.
- Reducing manual configuration errors.

Export Process

1. Navigate to **System Update Sets → Local Update Sets**.
2. Open the project Update Set.
3. Click **Export to XML**.
4. Save the exported `.xml` file.
5. Upload the exported file to this repository.

Expected File

After exporting, this folder will contain a file similar to:

Project_RBAC_Update_Set.xml
Benefits

- Easy deployment
- Configuration backup
- Reusable project package
- Faster migration between environments
 Note

The XML Update Set file will be uploaded after completing the project implementation and exporting it from the ServiceNow instance.
